div.p:
The Governments of the Republics represented at the Sixth International
                    Conference of American States, held in the city of Habana, Republic of Cuba, in
                    the year 1928;

Considering that neutrality is the juridical situation of states which do not
                    take part in the hostilities, and that it creates rights and imposes obligations
                    of impartiality, which should be regulated;

Recognizing that international solidarity requires that the liberty of commerce
                    should be always respected, avoiding as far as possible unnecessary burdens for
                    the neutrals;
